dcterms:description: QM9 is a dataset composed of 133,885 compounds made of up to 9 heavy atoms (C, O, N, F), plus the hydrogens bound to them, for a maximum size of 29 atoms. Each molecule is represented as an undirected graph, where each vertex corresponds to an atom and each edge corresponds to a chemical bond.
dcterms:title: QM9

dcterms:description: Zinc is a dataset composed of 249,455 organic molecules of up to 38 heavy atoms (C, O, N, F, P, S, Cl, I, Br). It includes explicit labeling of ring bonds as aromatic when part of an aromatic ring.
dcterms:title: Zinc
